text: Aleksandr Ivanovich Timoshinin (, 20 May 1948 â€“ 26 November 2021) was a Russian rower. He was born in Moscow. He competed for the Soviet Union in the 1968 Summer Olympics and in the 1972 Summer Olympics. He won two gold medals at each Olympic event. Timoshinin died on 26 November 2021, at the age of 73. ==References== Category:1948 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympic gold medalists for the Soviet Union Category:Sportspeople from Moscow Category:Soviet rowers
